				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Chlorine is a highly effective method of disinfection. It can kill most bacteria, viruses, and parasites when added to water. However, it produces small amounts of chemicals called 'disinfection by-products' if the source water has higher levels of dirt or germs. Chlorine is also used up quickly in water systems. It is used to manufacture household chlorine bleach, which can whiten and disinfect clothes and surfaces.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">氯是一种高效的消毒方法。加入水中后，它可以杀死大多数细菌、病毒和寄生虫。但是，如果原水中的污垢或病菌含量较高，它就会产生少量称为 &quot;消毒副产品 &quot;的化学物质。氯在供水系统中也会很快消耗掉。它被用来制造家用氯漂白剂，可以美白和消毒衣物和表面。</common:generalComment>
